column12: Measurement condition : Clear; Clear , No Precipitation , Moderate Wind Blowing Cross Stream
column13: Open water conditions, periods of lake ice flowing in the river.
column14: Measured approx 450m downstream where it was wadable.  Normally measurement would be taken at a cross section right at the gauge but did not have a boat motor to cross the river as it had broken down.  Used book end and mid HG values for MGH, no considerable differenence when all HG values in mmnt are used. 1.022 old offset, 1.009 new offset.  Surveyed water level where boat launch enters the water. Mid-section
HG: 2.079 Surge: 0.000  * The uncertainty value is equivalent to the surge value in eHSN.  No Reset (NR)

column12: Measurement condition : No Flow; Partly Cloudy , No Precipitation , Light Wind
column14: Drilled three holes evenly spaced across measurement transect approximately 100m downstream of HWY1 bridge in order to confirm zero flow. Water welled into holes but unable to get FT2 under ice. Poked around with ice bar and determined no or minimal effective depth. Zero flow considered confirmed. Drilling more holes not sustainable due to wrecking auger tip on rocks basically every hole. Times for MGH are approximate based on inReach tracking points. Stage trace is very stable.
HG: 2.075 Surge: 0.000  * The uncertainty value is equivalent to the surge value in eHSN.

column12: Measurement condition : No Flow; Partly Cloudy , No Precipitation , Calm Wind
column13: Complete ice cover conditions at control (gauge). Complete ice cover conditions downstream at measurement section. Ice thickness 0.30-0.42m. Depth 0.40-0.56m. Effective depths approximately 10-15cm. Overflow on ice surface. Moderate slush in measurement holes.
column14: FlowTracker2 measurement approximately 300m downstream of HWY1 bridge. Confirmed zero flow across the entire transect. @ Uncertainty: IVE method, 2-sigma value (2 x Uncertainty Value reported in *.ft File). @ DWL obtained twice due to high closure error on the first run. Second DWL completed using a series of small loops circuit, limited remaining daylight. Old offset = 1.015m. Reset 1811MST. New offset = 1.022m.  Mid-section

column12: Measurement condition : Clear; Smokey , No Precipitation , Very Light Wind
column13: Some vegetation on left bank near gauge but suspect impact on discharge would be minimal. Velocities too slow for boat measurement near gauge, controlling boat to ensure smooth transects would have been extraordinarily challenging. Too deep for wading measurement. Too wide for bank-to-bank tagline measurement. Assessed section approx 1km down near cemetery, section is very braided and rocky, with some deep sections with high flow, but mostly shallow low/negative velocity sections with possibility of unmeasurable flow through rocks (pictures SIT3,SIT4,SIT5). Potential wading measurement section at other stages but likely poor today. Good wading section at winter measurement section downstream of NWT HWY1 bridge (pictures SIT7,SIT8,SIT9). Rocky/bouldery riverbed.
column14: Good FlowTracker 2 measurement approximately 115m downstream of NWT HWY1 bridge. No significant QA/QC concerns. Some angled flow in the middle. Max %Q 8%.  @ Uncertainty: IVE method, 2-sigma value (2 x Uncertainty Value reported in *.ft File). @ Old offset = 1.024, reset 0942MST, new offset = 1.015. Mid-section
HG: 2.229 Surge: 0.002  * The uncertainty value is equivalent to the surge value in eHSN.  Reset (RS)
HG: 2.362 Surge: 0.002  * The uncertainty value is equivalent to the surge value in eHSN.  No Reset (NR)

column12: Measurement condition : Clear; Partly Cloudy , No Precipitation , Light Wind Blowing Downstream
column13: No vegetation that would impact flow at this time. Still ice on the lake except around edges.
column14: Fair-good StreamPro measurement. Qrev warns of excessive movement on right edge, moving bed test critical error, and extrapolation uncertainty warning. Excessive movement very difficult to avoid given low water velocities, this was as smooth a transect as could be hoped for with manned boat in these conditions. If stage drops significantly later in the season, suggest bringing two taglines for shore to shore taagline measurement or assess potential wading sections just downstream around the bend or elsewhere. @ Uncertainty: QRev Uncertainty Analysis (DS Mueller, 2016), 2-sigma value (1 x Uncertainty Value reported in *.xml File). @ ADCP by Moving Boat

column12: Measurement condition : Ice; Cloudy , Moderate Snow , Light Wind Blowing Cross Stream
column13: Consistent ice at measurement section downstream HWY1 bridge, average = 0 91m. Between 25-50% ice cover at gauge.
column14: Fair StreamPro measurement approx. 50m downstream of HWY1 bridge. Channel frozen to bottom in the middle, flow divided into left and right channels w/ no flow in middle. Drilled holes to define the edges of the frozen to bottom section in the middle as much as possible. Significant change in depth since last visit in January, it seems. Some manual panels entered with zero velocity as un-measurable effective depths. Broke up panels exceeding 10% to within reason but a few remain, highest 14% close to right bank.  @ Uncertainty: ISO method, 2-sigma value (1 x Uncertainty Value reported in *.xml File). @ Offset = 1.024m. SL2 removed. SL3 SN 2108815 installed. Disconnected SL2 1700. First SL3 HG reading 1745. Data in between is invalid. CS450 SN 14010496. Mid-section

column12: Measurement condition : Ice; Partly Cloudy , No Precipitation , Calm Wind
column13: Average ice thickness 0.88m. Min 0.78, max 1. Stratified ice layers - a fairly thick overflow ice layer separated from ice below by approx 2-4cm of water in between, unsure if there is flow in this layer, would likely be impossible to measure. No or minimal water for the first 10m from left bank. Holes drilled with either no water/rocks or thick slush below - no flow. Right measurement edge well defined with hole drilled at 60m mark - dry until hit rocks on bottom.
column14: Fair-good StreamPro measurement approx 50m downstream of HWY1 bridge, adjacacent to boat launch. Some flow angles. Unsure of cause - seemed to be boulders in certain spots - hit a couple of larger rocks with drill even in middle of river. That or sandbar or something else may be causing flow angles. Not totally sure of riverbed composition at this location. @ Uncertainty: ISO method, 2-sigma value (1 x Uncertainty Value reported in *.xml File). @ MGH calculated from Telemetry - no SRC applied as gauge reset on Jan 30.  Mid-section
HG: 2.354 Surge: 0.003  * The uncertainty value is equivalent to the surge value in eHSN.  No Reset (NR)

column12: Measurement condition : Clear; Partly Cloudy , No Precipitation , Light Wind Blowing Upstream
column13: OPEN AND CLEAR. Winds from downstream obviously impacting surface layer of river which appeared to be flowing backwards.
column14: MEASURED BY BOAT USING CRESTLINER AND 6 HP YAMAHA. Fair to good RiverPro measurement adjcant to gauge. Very slow velocities, difficulty maintaining smooth ship track but managed fairly well by physically holding the ADCP to prevent excess rotation. Qrev has systest warning - one of the ADCP tests failed the first attempt but all passed on the second attempt - no issue. Moving bed test warning - velocities below recommended for loop test. Did not see this warning in WR2 so didn't realize but not sure if would have been able to anchor for stationary test - shallow rocky riverbed, did consider at the time of measurement.   @ Uncertainty: QRev Uncertainty Analysis (DS Mueller, 2016), 2-sigma value (1 x Uncertainty Value reported in *.xml File). @ MGH calculated in excel from logger file and added using mean mmnt time. Took mean SRC from 1045/1230 for MGH which was zero, would have been <0.003 either way. Performed benchmark tie in separate eHSN using conventional leveling - unable to use multiple level types in the same eHSN. ADCP by Moving Boat
HG: 2.352 Surge: 0.002  * The uncertainty value is equivalent to the surge value in eHSN.  No Reset (NR)
